      • setParams

        public void setParams(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> params)
        The parameters are accepted as a key/value pair of a HashMap. Example: key = "-output" / value = "file.txt" results to ... -output file.txt ...
        1. If the there is no value for a param like for "-XMLf" leave the corresponding value null or set the blank string "";
        2. If the there is no key for a param like "/folder/file.txt" leave the corresponding key null or set the blank string "";
        Specified by:
        setParams in interface Extractor
        Parameters:
        params - the params to set
